# BMAD Method (v6.0.0-Beta.8)

BMAD is the AI workflow orchestration system installed in this project.

## Configuration
- Config: `_bmad/core/config.yaml` (user_name: Solar, language: English)
- Output folder: `_bmad-output/`

## Available Workflows & Tasks

| Name | Code | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| Brainstorming | BSP | Generate ideas via creative techniques. Load `_bmad/core/workflows/brainstorming/workflow.md` |
| Party Mode | PM | Multi-agent discussions. Load `_bmad/core/workflows/party-mode/workflow.md` |
| Help | BH | Show next steps. Load `_bmad/core/tasks/help.md` |
| Index Docs | ID | Create doc index. Load `_bmad/core/tasks/index-docs.xml` |
| Shard Document | SD | Split large docs. Load `_bmad/core/tasks/shard-doc.xml` |
| Editorial Review - Prose | EP | Copy-edit text. Load `_bmad/core/tasks/editorial-review-prose.xml` |
| Editorial Review - Structure | ES | Reorganize docs. Load `_bmad/core/tasks/editorial-review-structure.xml` |
| Adversarial Review | AR | Critical review. Load `_bmad/core/tasks/review-adversarial-general.xml` |

## Execution Pattern
1. Load `_bmad/core/config.yaml` first for session variables
2. Load the task/workflow file referenced above
3. Follow instructions exactly
4. Save outputs to `_bmad-output/`
